# Nimbus ŌĆö Cursor Rules

## Project Identity

Nimbus is a local-first AI agent framework. The machine is the source of truth. Cloud providers are connectors ŌĆö useful, but never primary and never unconditionally trusted.

Every design decision is evaluated against one question: **Does this return agency to the user, or does it erode it?**

---

## Non-Negotiables ŌĆö Reject any suggestion that violates these

### 1. Local-First Principle
- The local SQLite index is the authoritative catalog
- Cloud APIs are called only when freshness is required
- No user data or credentials leave the machine without explicit user action
- No Nimbus cloud service, no Nimbus relay, no telemetry by default

### 2. HITL Consent Gate ŌĆö Structural Enforcement
- The consent gate lives in `packages/gateway/src/engine/executor.ts`
- `HITL_REQUIRED` is a `ReadonlySet<string>` frozen at module load ŌĆö `Object.freeze(new Set([...]))`
- It is not a prompt instruction. It is not configurable at runtime. It cannot be bypassed.
- Any suggestion to "skip" or "bypass" or "configure" the consent gate is invalid
- HITL-required actions: `file.delete`, `file.move`, `file.rename`, `file.create`, `email.send`, `email.draft.send`, `email.draft.create`, `calendar.event.create`, `calendar.event.delete`, `photo.delete`, `onedrive.delete`, `onedrive.move`, `slack.message.post`, `teams.message.post`, `teams.message.postChat`, `linear.issue.create`, `linear.issue.update`, `linear.comment.create`, `jira.issue.create`, `jira.issue.update`, `jira.comment.add`, `notion.page.create`, `notion.page.update`, `notion.block.append`, `notion.comment.create`, `confluence.page.create`, `confluence.page.update`, `confluence.comment.add`; Phase 3 adds: `jenkins.build.trigger`, `jenkins.build.abort`, `github_actions.run.trigger`, `github_actions.run.cancel`, `circleci.pipeline.trigger`, `circleci.job.cancel`, `gitlab.pipeline.retry`, `gitlab.pipeline.cancel`, `aws.ecs.service.update`, `aws.lambda.invoke`, `aws.ec2.instance.stop`, `aws.ec2.instance.start`, `azure.app_service.restart`, `azure.aks.node_pool.scale`, `gcp.cloud_run.deploy`, `gcp.gke.workload.restart`, `iac.terraform.apply`, `iac.terraform.destroy`, `iac.cloudformation.deploy`, `iac.pulumi.up`, `kubernetes.rollout.restart`, `kubernetes.pod.delete`, `kubernetes.deployment.scale`, `pagerduty.incident.acknowledge`, `pagerduty.incident.resolve`, `pagerduty.incident.escalate` ŌĆö `packages/gateway/src/engine/executor.ts` is always authoritative
- Audit log is written BEFORE execution, not after

### 3. No Plaintext Credentials
- OAuth tokens, API keys, and secrets go into the OS-native Vault ONLY
- Vault implementations: Windows DPAPI, macOS Keychain, Linux libsecret
- `NimbusVault.get()` returns `string | null` ŌĆö never throws on absence
- Pino logger MUST have `redact` config covering `*.token`, `*.secret`, `oauth.*`, `*.password`, `*.key`
- No credential in: logs, IPC responses, error messages, config files, or plaintext env vars (only injected into extension child processes)

### 4. MCP as the Connector Standard
- The Engine (Mastra agent) is an MCP client ŌĆö it never calls cloud APIs directly
- Every external service integration is an MCP server process
- This makes connectors independently replaceable and every tool call auditable
- Never add a direct API call from `packages/gateway/src/engine/`

### 5. Platform Equality
- Windows 10+, macOS 13+, Ubuntu 22.04+ are equally first-class
- Platform-specific code lives exclusively in `packages/gateway/src/platform/`
- `PlatformServices` interface is the only abstraction boundary
- Business logic must never import from `./win32`, `./darwin`, or `./linux` directly
- A feature that works on macOS and "probably works" on Windows is a defect

### 6. AGPL-3.0 / MIT Dual License
- All packages except `packages/sdk/` are `"license": "AGPL-3.0-only"`
- `packages/sdk/` (`@nimbus-dev/sdk`) is `"license": "MIT"` ŌĆö this is intentional and load-bearing
- Never change the `license` field in gateway, cli, or mcp-connectors package.json
- Any contribution to core packages must be AGPL-3.0 compatible

