## Architecture Patterns

### Package Boundaries (dependency rules)
```
packages/gateway/          ŌåÉ @nimbus/gateway ŌĆö AGPL ŌĆö never import from cli or ui
packages/cli/              ŌåÉ @nimbus/cli ŌĆö AGPL ŌĆö IPC only, no direct gateway source imports
packages/ui/               ŌåÉ @nimbus/ui ŌĆö AGPL ŌĆö IPC only, no direct gateway source imports
packages/sdk/              ŌåÉ @nimbus-dev/sdk ŌĆö MIT ŌĆö no imports from gateway/cli/ui
packages/mcp-connectors/*  ŌåÉ AGPL ŌĆö depend on @nimbus-dev/sdk only
```

The CLI and UI communicate with the Gateway exclusively over JSON-RPC 2.0 IPC (domain socket on Unix, named pipe on Windows). They do not import gateway TypeScript source.

### Subsystem Locations
| Component | Path |
|---|---|
| HITL gate | `packages/gateway/src/engine/executor.ts` |
| PAL entry | `packages/gateway/src/platform/index.ts` |
| Vault interface | `packages/gateway/src/vault/index.ts` |
| Local index | `packages/gateway/src/index/` |
| Connector mesh | `packages/gateway/src/connectors/` |
| Extension registry | `packages/gateway/src/extensions/` |
| IPC server | `packages/gateway/src/ipc/` |
| CLI commands | `packages/cli/src/commands/` |
| IPC client | `packages/cli/src/ipc-client/` |

### Extension Security Model
- Extensions are child processes ŌĆö `Bun.spawn` with explicit env
- Extensions receive credentials ONLY for their declared service (env injection from Vault)
- Extensions cannot access `NimbusVault` directly ŌĆö no Vault API exposed across process boundary
- Two hashes are verified on every Gateway startup: SHA-256 of `nimbus.extension.json` (`manifest_hash`) AND SHA-256 of the compiled entry point file (`entry_hash`)
- Either hash mismatch ŌåÆ extension disabled before process spawn, `ERROR` log entry identifies the file
- `nimbus.extension.json` permissions are immutable at runtime
- Network permissions declared in the manifest are validated at install time but not enforced at kernel/syscall level in v1 ŌĆö full isolation planned for Phase 5

